# SQL Query Buddy - Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env and add your actual API keys

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: SECURITY NOTICE
# =============================================================================
# - API keys are ONLY loaded from this .env file (never from config files)
# - NEVER commit the .env file to version control (already in .gitignore)
# - At least ONE valid API key is REQUIRED for the server to start
# - The server will fail to start if no valid API keys are configured
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# API KEYS - Get your keys from the links below
# =============================================================================

# OpenAI API Key (RECOMMENDED - Required for embeddings used by other providers)
# Get key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Note: Requires payment/credits. New accounts get $5 free trial credit.
# If you use Cohere or AI21 as your LLM, you still need OpenAI for embeddings.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Cohere API Key (Optional - Free tier available)
# Get key: https://dashboard.cohere.com/api-keys
# Note: Generous free tier for development. Requires OpenAI key for embeddings.
COHERE_API_KEY=

# AI21 Labs API Key (Optional)
# Get key: https://studio.ai21.com/account/api-key
# Note: Requires OpenAI key for embeddings.
AI21_API_KEY=

# Google AI Studio API Key (RECOMMENDED - Free tier available)
# Get key: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# Note: Permanent free tier with rate limits. Great for getting started!
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# Anthropic API Key (Optional - Free credits for new accounts)
# Get key: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Note: New accounts get $5+ in free credits
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Mistral API Key (Optional - Free developer tier)
# Get key: https://console.mistral.ai/
# Note: Free developer tier with rate limits
MISTRAL_API_KEY=

# Groq API Key (RECOMMENDED - Free developer tier)
# Get key: https://console.groq.com/keys
# Note: Free tier with extremely fast inference (LPU-based)
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Together AI API Key (Optional - Free credits for new accounts)
# Get key: https://api.together.xyz/settings/api-keys
# Note: New accounts get $25 in free credits
TOGETHER_API_KEY=

# OpenRouter API Key (Optional - Free tier available)
# Get key: https://openrouter.ai/keys
# Note: Permanent free tier (~50 requests/day)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# SERVER CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# Port the server will run on
# Default: 3001 (will be used if this line is commented out or removed)
# You can change this to any available port
PORT=3001

# =============================================================================
# QUICK START GUIDE
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    - Windows: copy .env.example .env
#    - Linux/Mac: cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and add at least ONE API key:
#    - RECOMMENDED for beginners: GOOGLE_API_KEY or GROQ_API_KEY (both free)
#    - For production: OPENAI_API_KEY (requires payment but most reliable)
#
# 3. Start the server:
#    npm start
#
# 4. If the server fails to start, check the error message for which API
#    keys are missing and where to get them.
#
# 5. Visit: http://localhost:3001
#
# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
# - Server exits with "No valid API keys configured"?
#   → You need to add at least one API key to the .env file
#
# - "API key is invalid" error?
#   → Double-check your API key is correct (no extra spaces)
#   → Verify the key is active in the provider's dashboard
#
# - Want to add more providers later?
#   → Just add the key to .env and restart the server
#   → Or use the web interface to add keys without restarting
#
# For more details, see README.md
